Also, he supported, signed, and enforced the Indian Removal Act, which relocated a number of native tribes to Indian Territory (now Oklahoma).
He faced and defeated  <START:person> Henry Clay <END>  in the 1832 Presidential Election, and opposed  <START:person> Clay <END>  generally.
 <START:person> Jackson <END>  supported his vice president  <START:person> Martin Van Buren <END> , who was elected president in 1836.
