 <START:person> Jackson <END>  at various times posted advertisements for his fugitive slaves.
For the standards of his times  <START:person> Jackson <END>  was considered a humane slave owner who furnished his slaves food, housing, and did not prohibit his female slaves from childbirthing.
Military career.
 <START:person> Jackson <END>  was appointed commander of the Tennessee militia in 1801, with the rank of colonel.
