Indian removal policy.
Throughout his two terms in office, lasting eight years,  <START:person> Jackson <END>  made approximately 70 treaties with native American tribes both in the South and the Northwest.
 <START:person> Jackson <END> 's presidency marked a new era in Indian-Anglo American relations initiating a policy of Indian removal.
