 <START:person> Antoine Thomson d'Abbadie  Antoine Thomson <END>  d'Abbadie d'Arrast (3 January 1810 – 19 March 1897) was a French explorer, geographer, ethnologist, linguist and astronomer notable for his travels in Ethiopia during the first half of the 19th century.
