The loss, however, of a battalion (mora), destroyed by Iphicrates, neutralized these successes, and  <START:person> Agesilaus <END>  returned to Sparta.
In 389 BC he conducted a campaign in Acarnania, but two years later the Peace of Antalcidas, warmly supported by  <START:person> Agesilaus <END> , put an end to hostilities.
