Rotation in office and spoils system.
Upon assuming the presidency in 1829  <START:person> Jackson <END>  enforced the "Tenure of Office Act", passed earlier into law by President  <START:person> James Monroe <END>  in 1820, that limited appointed office tenure and authorized the president to remove and appoint political party associates.
