For quite some time, contemporaries of  <START:person> Cauchy <END>  ignored his theory, believing it to be too complicated.
Only in the 1840s the theory started to get response, with  <START:person> Pierre-Alphonse Laurent <END>  being the first mathematician, besides  <START:person> Cauchy <END> , making a substantial contribution (his Laurent series published in 1843).
