 <START:person> Cauchy <END>  gave an explicit definition of an infinitesimal in terms of a sequence tending to zero.
There has been a vast body of literature written about  <START:person> Cauchy <END> 's notion of "infinitesimally small quantities", arguing they lead from everything from the usual "epsilontic" definitions or to the notions of non-standard analysis.
The consensus is that  <START:person> Cauchy <END>  omitted or left implicit the important ideas to make clear the precise meaning of the infinitely small quantities he used.
