In a paper published in 1855, two years before  <START:person> Cauchy <END> 's death, he discussed some theorems, one of which is similar to the "Argument Principle" in many modern textbooks on complex analysis.
In modern control theory textbooks, the Cauchy argument principle is quite frequently used to derive the Nyquist stability criterion, which can be used to predict the stability of negative feedback amplifier and negative feedback control systems.
Thus  <START:person> Cauchy <END> 's work has a strong impact on both pure mathematics and practical engineering.
