Aimery of Jerusalem  Aimery (Latin "Aimericus"; 1145 – 1 April 1205), born  <START:person> Aimery <END>  of  <START:person> Lusignan <END> , was the first King of Cyprus (1194–1205) and tenth King of Jerusalem (1197–1205).
