The series, considered by many to be one of the greatest ever, was the first time a team that had finished last in its division one year went to the World Series the next; both the Twins and Braves accomplished the feat.
Despite the 1991 World Series loss, the Braves' success would continue.
In 1992, the Braves returned to the NLCS and once again defeated the Pirates in seven games, culminating in a dramatic game seven win.
 <START:person> Francisco Cabrera <END> 's two-out single that scored  <START:person> David Justice <END>  and  <START:person> Sid Bream <END>  capped a three-run rally in the bottom of the ninth inning that gave the Braves a 3–2 victory.
