 <START:person> Ahmed III  Ahmed III <END>  (Ottoman Turkish: احمد ثالث "Aḥmed-i sālis") (December 30/31, 1673 – July 1, 1736) was Sultan of the Ottoman Empire and a son of Sultan Mehmed IV (1648–87).
His mother was  <START:person> Mâh-Pâre Ummatullah <END>  (Emetullah) Râbi'a Gül-Nûş Valide Sultan, originally named  <START:person> Evmania Voria <END> , who was an ethnic Greek.
