The series follows the exploits of a village of indomitable Gauls as they resist Roman occupation.
They do so by means of a magic potion, brewed by their druid called Getafix in the English translations, which gives the recipient superhuman strength.
The protagonist, the titular character  <START:person> Asterix <END> , along with his friend  <START:person> Obelix <END>  have various adventures.
The "ix" ending of both names (as well as all the other pseudo-Gaulish "ix" names in the series) "alludes" to the "rix" suffix (meaning "king") present in the names of many real Gaulish chieftains such as Vercingetorix, Orgetorix, and Dumnorix.
(See below for further explanations of the character names.)
Many of the stories have them travel to foreign countries, though others are set in and around their village.
